org.tair.sql.expression
Class ParameterizedSubqueryExpression

java.lang.Object
  org.tair.sql.expression.Expression
      org.tair.sql.expression.SubqueryExpression
          org.tair.sql.expression.ParameterizedSubqueryExpression
All Implemented Interfaces:
IExpression, IMultipleParameterExpression, ISubqueryExpression
public abstract class ParameterizedSubqueryExpression
extends SubqueryExpression
implements IMultipleParameterExpression

An abstract subquery expression that has one or more parameters (JDBC ? expressions) in the query, usually in the WHERE clause; subclass this class and override the bind() method with the appropriate JDBC binding code.

Author:
Robert J. Muller

bind

public abstract int bind(java.sql.PreparedStatement stmt,
                         int index)
                  throws java.sql.SQLException
Description copied from interface: IMultipleParameterExpression
Bind the value to the expression parameter ? within the prepared statement using the correct JDBC binding method for the type; the concrete instantiation of the template implements this method. The method returns the last index bound.

Specified by:
bind in interface IMultipleParameterExpression
Parameters:
stmt - the JDBC prepared statement containing the SQL statement parameter to which to bind a value
index - the 1-based index of the parameter to set within the complete SQL statement
Returns:
the last index bound
Throws:
java.sql.SQLException - when there is a problem binding a value to a parameter
